{
  "texts": [
    "AI simulators can allow trainees to practice an extensive range of surgical scenarios, ranging routine cases to advanced complications, with no threat to real patients and immediate feedback.",
    "This can not only speed up their learning curve, but can also foster a sense of competence and confidence which is essential for success in the operation theatre.In addition to its role as a training tool, VR simulation has significant applications in pre-surgical planning and performance assessment.",
    "During pre-operative planning, VR enables patient-specific strategy development, aiding in procedure planning and simulating surgical outcomes to improve decision-making and reduce risks [108,109].",
    "For instance, Friedrich et al.",
    "introduced a VR approach for implant generation using advanced 3D models [108]."
  ]
}